===2000 census===
As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2" /> of 2000, there were 2,498 people, 981 households, and 669 families residing in the town. The population density was {{convert|2,357.8|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. There were 1,090 housing units at an average density of {{convert|1,028.8|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of the town was 65.57% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 19.22% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 12.69% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.12% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.56% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 1.84% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 1.48% of the population.{{citation needed|date=June 2025}}

There were 981 households, out of which 34.5% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 41.3% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 21.2% had a female householder with no husband present, and 31.8% were non-families. 28.8% of all households were made up of individuals, and 11.9% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.55 and the average family size was 3.14.{{citation needed|date=June 2025}}

In the town, the population was spread out, with 28.2% under the age of 18, 10.3% from 18 to 24, 27.5% from 25 to 44, 22.7% from 45 to 64, and 11.3% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 34 years. For every 100 females there were 88.1 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 81.2 males.{{citation needed|date=June 2025}}

The median income for a household in the town was $22,015, and the median income for a family was $27,460. Males had a median income of $26,313 versus $18,854 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the town was $10,177. About 28.5% of families and 31.6% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 37.7% of those under age 18 and 31.2% of those age 65 or over.{{citation needed|date=June 2025}}

